(144, 'phrasal', '(adjective)', '/ˈfreɪzl/', 'forming or relating to a group of words that is part of, rather than the whole of, a sentence / forming or relating to a short group of words that are often used together and have a particular meaning', 'Both dialects have the same phrasal ordering but some different lexical items.\r\nPhrasal sets like \"shut up\" and \"kick the bucket\" cannot be understood as a sum of their parts.', '', '', '2024-01-09 07:33:57', 'view/uploads/image/40_59_19_23_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/47_37_15_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(145, 'solid', '(adjective)', '/ˈsɑːlɪd/', 'chất rắn / đặc / nét liền', 'The planet Jupiter may have no solid surface at all.\r\nThe boat bumped against a solid object.\r\nShe had refused all solid food.\r\nThe collection and disposal of solid waste.\r\nIt was so cold that the stream had frozen solid.', '', '', '2024-01-09 07:44:07', 'view/uploads/image/07_44_14_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/07_44_14_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(146, 'solid foundation', '', '', 'nền tảng vững chắc', '', '', '', '2024-01-09 07:46:54', 'view/uploads/image/54_46_14_9_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(147, 'foundation', '(noun)', '/faʊnˈdeɪʃn/', 'a principle, an idea or a fact that something is based on and that it grows from / an organization that has been created in order to provide money for a particular group of people in need of help or for a particular type of study / an idea or fact that something is based on', 'solid foundation.\r\nthe foundation of a new state', '', '', '2024-01-09 07:49:17', 'view/uploads/image/17_49_14_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/17_49_14_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(148, 'rest', '(noun)', '/rest/', 'stop doing a particular activity or stop being active for a period of time in order to relax and get back your strength', 'I had a good night\'s rest.\r\nWe stopped for a well-earned rest.\r\nThe country enjoys friendly relations with the rest of the world.\r\nHow would you like to spend the rest of the day?', '', '', '2024-01-09 07:52:50', 'view/uploads/image/12_13_17_20_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/50_52_14_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(149, 'rest of', '(phrasal verb)', '', 'the part of something that remains', '', '', '', '2024-01-09 08:03:20', 'view/uploads/image/48_53_5_21_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(150, 'general skills', '', '', 'những kỹ năng cơ bản', '', '', '', '2024-01-09 08:09:46', 'view/uploads/image/26_53_5_21_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(151, 'problem-solving skills', '', '', 'kỹ năng giải quyết vấn đề', '', '', '', '2024-01-09 08:12:24', 'view/uploads/image/41_13_15_9_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(152, 'manipulation', '(noun)', '/məˌnɪpjuˈleɪʃn/', 'controlling someone or something to your own advantage, often unfairly or dishonestly / an act of controlling or moving something by using the hands / using something, often with a lot of skill', 'DOM manipulation\r\nThey have been accused of fraud and stock market manipulations.\r\nOften a dislocated finger can be fixed by manipulation.\r\n', '', '', '2024-01-09 08:19:05', 'view/uploads/image/05_19_15_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/05_19_15_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(153, 'fundamental', '(noun)', '/ˌfʌndəˈmentl/', 'forming the base, from which everything else develops / more important than anything else / being the most basic or most important thing on which other things depend', 'The fundamentals of modern physics.\r\nHe taught me the fundamentals of the job.', '', '', '2024-01-09 08:31:52', 'view/uploads/image/16_32_15_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/52_31_15_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(155, 'navigate', '(verb)', '/ˈnævɪɡeɪt/', 'to direct the way that a ship, aircraft, etc. will travel, or to find a direction across, along, or over an area of water or land, often by using a map / to move around a website or computer screen, or between websites or screens', 'Pigeons navigate less accurately when the earth\'s magnetic field is disturbed.\r\nShe became expert in driving and navigating across the desert.\r\nThese birds navigate by the sun.', '', '', '2024-01-09 08:48:20', 'view/uploads/image/20_48_15_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/20_48_15_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(156, 'advanced', '(adjective)', '/ədˈvænst/', 'modern and well developed / at a higher, more difficult level', 'Scientists are working on highly advanced technology to replace fossil fuels.\r\nIt is a technologically advanced society.\r\nThere were only three of us on the advanced course.', '', '', '2024-01-09 08:52:44', 'view/uploads/image/44_52_15_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/44_52_15_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(157, 'right away', '', '', '<=> immediately', '', '', '', '2024-01-09 09:40:55', 'view/uploads/image/59_05_16_21_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(158, 'along', '(preposition)', '/əˈlɔːŋ/', 'dọc theo / dọc', 'They walked slowly along the road.\r\nI looked along the shelves for the book I needed.', '', '', '2024-01-09 09:58:42', 'view/uploads/image/42_58_16_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/42_58_16_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(159, 'along with', '', '', 'cùng với', '', '', '', '2024-01-09 09:59:02', 'view/uploads/image/02_59_16_9_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(160, 'preposition', '(noun)', '/ˌprepəˈzɪʃn/', 'in grammar, a word that is used before a noun, a noun phrase, or a pronoun, connecting it to another word / a word that connects a noun, a noun phrase, or a pronoun to another word, esp. to a verb, another noun, or an adjective / giới từ', 'In the sentences \"We jumped in the lake\", and \"She drove slowly down the track\", \"in\" and \"down\" are prepositions.', '', '', '2024-01-09 10:02:44', 'view/uploads/image/17_43_5_21_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/44_02_17_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(161, 'crucial', '(adjective)', '/ˈkruːʃl/', 'extremely important or necessary / extremely important because many other things depend on it', 'The next few weeks are going to be crucial.\r\nPrivate security cameras can prove crucial in some investigations.\r\nParents play a crucial role in preparing their child for school.\r\nThis step is a crucial part of the process.', '', '', '2024-01-09 12:49:25', 'view/uploads/image/25_49_19_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/25_49_19_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(162, 'it doesn\'t matter as long as', '', '', 'nó không quan trọng miễn là', '', '', '', '2024-01-09 12:58:02', '', '', '', 0),
(163, 'matter', '(noun)', '/ˈmætər/', 'a situation or subject that is being dealt with or considered / a substance or things of a particular type', 'Allen denied any knowledge of the matter.\r\nDo you find the subject matter of the book (= the subject that the book deals with) interesting?', '', '', '2024-01-09 13:03:04', 'view/uploads/image/04_03_20_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/04_03_20_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(164, 'long', '(adjective)', '/lɔːŋ/', 'being a distance between two points that is more than average or usual / continuing for a large amount of time', 'She had long dark hair.\r\nHe walked down the long corridor.\r\nIt was the world\'s longest bridge.\r\nWe\'re a long way from anywhere here.\r\nIt\'s a long way away.', '', '', '2024-01-09 13:06:42', 'view/uploads/image/45_08_20_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/42_06_20_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(165, 'as', '(preposition)', '/əz/', 'như / dưới dạng', 'They were all dressed as clowns.\r\nThe bomb was disguised as a package.', '', '', '2024-01-09 13:08:32', 'view/uploads/image/34_48_5_21_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/32_08_20_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(166, 'stress', '(noun)', '/stres/', 'great worry caused by a difficult situation, or something that causes this condition / a difficult situation caused by too much being needed or expected from a system, resource', 'An overcrowded workplace can be a major source of stress.\r\nHe\'s been under a lot of stress lately.\r\nParenting under stress can be extremely difficult.\r\nThe incident has caused enormous stress and anxiety to my family.\r\nWe all sometimes struggle with the stresses and strains of daily life.\r\nHow can we help young people cope with the stress of exams?\r\nThe city is finding it hard to cope with stress on its housing supply.', '', '', '2024-01-09 13:15:05', 'view/uploads/image/05_15_20_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/05_15_20_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(167, 'otherwise', '(adverb)', '/ˈʌðərwaɪz/', 'used after an order or suggestion to show what the result will be if you do not follow that order or suggestion / differently, or in another way', 'My parents lent me the money. Otherwise, I couldn\'t have afforded the trip.\r\nShut the window, otherwise it\'ll get too cold in here.', '', '', '2024-01-09 13:20:45', 'view/uploads/image/45_20_20_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/45_20_20_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(168, 'figure out', '(phrasal verb)', '', 'to finally understand something or someone, or find the solution to a problem after a lot of thought / to understand someone or something, or to find the answer to something by thinking', 'I can\'t figure out why he did it.\r\nCan you figure out how to open this?', '', '', '2024-01-09 13:24:23', 'view/uploads/image/12_30_20_9_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(169, 'figure', '(noun)', '/ˈfɪɡjər/', 'the symbol for a number or an amount expressed in numbers / the shape of the human body, or a person / a painting, drawing, or model of a person', 'Can you read this figure? Is it a three or an eight?\r\nI could see two tall figures in the distance.\r\nShe\'s got a beautiful figure.', '', '', '2024-01-09 13:29:12', 'view/uploads/image/50_29_20_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/50_29_20_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(170, 'don\'t beat yourself up', '', '', 'đừng tự trách bản thân', '', '', '', '2024-01-09 13:36:49', 'view/uploads/image/49_48_5_21_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(171, 'cover', '(verb)', '/ˈkʌvər/', 'to put or spread something over something, or to lie on the surface of something / to deal with or direct attention to something / to report the news about a particular important event / to protect someone against loss, damage, accident, or having something stolen / to make a recording of a song or tune that has already been recorded by someone else', 'She covered him with a blanket.\r\nDo these parking restrictions cover residents as well as visitors?\r\nShe\'s covering the American election for BBC television.\r\nDoes your travel insurance cover you for the loss or theft of cash?\r\nI think more singers have covered \"Yesterday\" than any other song.', '', '', '2024-01-09 13:52:43', 'view/uploads/image/43_52_20_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/43_52_20_9_1_2024_audio.ogg', '', 0),
(172, 'move on', '(phrasal verb)', '', 'chuyển sang / tiếp tục', '', '', '', '2024-01-09 14:04:24', 'view/uploads/image/12_46_5_21_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(173, 'take a note', '', '', 'to write something down or remember it carefully', 'I\'ll just take a note of your name and address.', '', '', '2024-01-09 14:09:53', 'view/uploads/image/24_05_15_21_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(174, 'material', '(noun)', '/məˈtɪriəl/', 'a physical substance that things can be made from / information used when writing something such as a book, or information produced in various forms to help people or to advertise products / cloth that can be used to make things such as clothes', 'Crude oil is used as the raw (= basic) material for making plastics.\r\nI\'m in the process of collecting material for an article that I\'m writing.\r\nHow much material will you need to make the skirt?', '', '', '2024-01-09 14:12:26', 'view/uploads/image/26_12_21_9_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/26_12_21_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(175, 'stick', '(verb)', '/stɪk/', 'dán / cắm', 'We used glue to stick the broken pieces together.\r\nI stuck the photos into an album.\r\nDon\'t stick your fingers through the bars of the cage.', '', '', '2024-01-09 14:19:42', 'view/uploads/image/47_08_5_24_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/42_19_21_9_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(177, 'note on', '(phrasal verb)', '', 'ghi chú về', '', '', '', '2024-01-10 07:06:57', 'view/uploads/image/18_12_5_24_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(178, 'theory', '(noun)', '/ˈθiːəri/', 'lý thuyết', 'The theories were tested on a sample of the population.\r\nNotes on theory concepts.', '', '', '2024-01-10 07:09:30', 'view/uploads/image/30_09_14_10_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/30_09_14_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(179, 'don\'t get overwhelmed', '', '', 'đừng bị choáng ngợp', '', '', '', '2024-01-10 07:14:04', 'view/uploads/image/04_14_14_10_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(180, 'overwhelm', '(verb)', '/ˌəʊvərˈwelm/', 'áp đảo / choáng ngợp', 'Government troops have overwhelmed the rebels and seized control of the capital.\r\nThe boxer relied on his power, pace, and pressure to overwhelm opponents.\r\nThe army was overwhelmed by the rebels.', '', '', '2024-01-10 07:19:17', 'view/uploads/image/31_00_17_20_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/17_19_14_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(181, 'efficient', '(adjective)', '/ɪˈfɪʃnt/', 'working or operating quickly and effectively in an organized way / working in a way that does not waste a resource (= something valuable such as fuel, water, or money)', 'The city\'s transport system is one of the most efficient in Europe.\r\nModern-day car engines are much more efficient.', '', '', '2024-01-10 07:24:22', 'view/uploads/image/49_49_14_21_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/22_24_14_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(182, 'don\'t get me wrong', '', '', 'đừng hiểu lầm tôi', '', '', '', '2024-01-10 07:29:09', 'view/uploads/image/09_29_14_10_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
(183, 'take a break', '(collocation)', '/teɪk ə breɪk/', 'to stop something for a short period, often to rest, to eat food, or to have a drink', 'You shouldn\'t drive for more than three hours without taking a break.', '', '', '2024-01-10 07:34:33', 'view/uploads/image/57_02_17_20_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 1),
(184, 'rewarding', '(adjective)', '/rɪˈwɔːrdɪŋ/', 'thoả mãn / bổ ích', 'it\'s so rewarding to see something', '', '', '2024-01-10 07:52:24', 'view/uploads/image/24_52_14_10_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/24_52_14_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(185, 'frustrated', '(adjective)', '/ˈfrʌstreɪtɪd/', 'thất vọng / bực bội / chán nản', 'It\'s very easy to get frustrated in this job.\r\nHis apathy just made her even more frustrated.\r\nHe stamped his foot in frustrated rage.\r\nA frustrated artist.', '', '', '2024-01-10 07:55:01', 'view/uploads/image/28_01_17_20_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/01_55_14_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(186, '', '', '', '', '', 'NPM stands for _ _ _', 'Node Package Manager', '2024-01-10 09:24:39', 'view/uploads/image/49_05_0_21_1_2024_image.jpg', '', '', 1),
(187, '', '', '', '', '', 'NVM stands for _ _ _', 'Node Version Manager', '2024-01-10 09:43:54', '', 'view/uploads/audio/56_49_23_20_3_2024_audio.mp3', '', 1),
(188, 'manager', '(noun)', '/ˈmænɪdʒər/', 'the person who is responsible for managing an organization / the person whose job is to organize and sometimes train a sports team / a computer program or system that helps you to control or organize a particular type of activity', 'I would like to speak to the manager.\r\nYou can click on a file in the file manager.', '', '', '2024-01-10 10:24:44', 'view/uploads/image/44_24_17_10_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/44_24_17_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(189, '', '', '', '', '', 'CMD stands for _ _', 'Command Prompt', '2024-01-10 10:59:20', '', '', '', 0),
(190, 'command', '(noun)', '/kəˈmænd/', 'an order, especially one given by a soldier / control over someone or something and responsibility for him, her, or it / an instruction to a computer to perform a particular action\r\n', 'He hated being in the army because he had to obey commands.\r\nLee took command of the Confederate Army in 1862.', '', '', '2024-01-10 11:12:20', 'view/uploads/image/39_51_14_21_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/20_12_18_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(191, 'version', '(noun)', '/ˈvɜːrʒn/', 'phiên bản', 'The latest version of the software package.\r\nThere are two versions of the game, a long one and a short one.\r\nThis is an edited version of the review.\r\nThe English version of the novel is due for publication next year.', '', '', '2024-01-10 12:47:10', 'view/uploads/image/34_33_22_21_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/10_47_19_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(192, 'wednesday', '(noun)', '/ˈwenzdeɪ/', 'thứ 4', '', '', '', '2024-01-10 12:55:03', 'view/uploads/image/03_55_19_10_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/03_55_19_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(193, 'syllabus', '(noun)', '/ˈsɪləbəs/', 'a list of the topics, books, etc. that students should study in a particular subject at school or college / giáo trình', 'American history will be on the syllabus next term.\r\nWhich novels are on the syllabus this year?', '', '', '2024-01-10 14:53:58', 'view/uploads/image/58_53_21_10_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/58_53_21_10_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0);
